# Per-listing landing pages live on the ctvreel-agent app at
# realestate.ctvhomes.com/l/{slug}. Burning that long subdomain into a CTV ad
# would be a mouthful — agents say "ctvhomes.com slash 419 Quaker" much more
# naturally.
#
# IMPORTANT: the order of these rules matters. Netlify processes them top to
# bottom, first match wins. Static-asset paths (_next, api) need to proxy
# straight through WITHOUT the /l/ prefix — otherwise the browser's request
# for /_next/static/chunks/foo.css gets rewritten to /l/_next/static/chunks/foo.css
# on Railway, which 404s, and the landing page renders unstyled.

# Next.js bundles (CSS, JS, fonts, image optimizer). Pass through unchanged.
/_next/*    https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/_next/:splat    200!

# API routes (lead submit, etc). Same — pass through unchanged.
/api/*      https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/api/:splat      200!

# Static assets the Next.js app might reference directly.
/favicon.ico   https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/favicon.ico  200

# Catch-all for everything else: /{slug} on the marketing domain maps to
# /l/{slug} on the Railway app, which renders the per-listing landing page.
# Netlify serves static files first, so marketing pages (pricing, plans,
# blog, etc.) keep getting served from here unchanged — only unknown paths
# fall through to this proxy.
/*          https://realestate.ctvhomes.com/l/:splat        200!
